fields.location: Furniture, room 133, case BY9, shelf LEDGE 2
fields.public_access_description: On loan to the Science Museum, London.
fields.history_note: Bequeathed by Mr Sannyer Atkin of 49, Elm Park Gardens, London SW10 - ‘A collection of 110 woodcarver’s and other tools with handles of various woods - English 19th century and after’. SA had a workshop where he carved ‘off the Fulham road’, and gave various items to the Museum over a period of years before his death in 1955. W.A. Thorpe in recommending acceptance noted that the tools have ‘in some cases an almost surgical fineness’.
